== Insider Tips from a Local

#tip-box[
  *Friendships Take Time:* Belgians can seem reserved at first. Don't mistake this for unfriendliness. It often takes more time to move from acquaintance to friend, but once you do, the friendships are typically deep and loyal.
]
#tip-box[
  *Embrace "La Belgique des Pigeons":* This phrase refers to the Belgian love of simple, everyday pleasures. A good beer with a friend, a walk in the park, a delicious meal. The culture values comfort, quality, and cosiness over flashiness.
]
#tip-box[
  *Explore Beyond the Capitals:* Brussels, Bruges, and Ghent are beautiful, but the real Belgium is also in the small towns. Explore the rolling hills of the Ardennes, the coastline, or the quiet villages of Flanders to get a fuller picture of the country.
]
#tip-box[
  *Master the Art of the Apéro:* The "apéro" (aperitif) is a cherished tradition. It's a pre-dinner drink with friends, often accompanied by small snacks like cheese, olives, or crisps. It’s a relaxed and essential part of social life.
]

